<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[952,1147,988,1014]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" pagination="486 - 501" refId="ref76282" refString="Shinohara, A. (1987 a) The sawfly genus Onycholyda (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) of Japan V. Kontyu, Tokyo, 55, 486 - 501." type="journal article" year="1987">Shinohara 1987a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Wei, M. - C." box="[1160,1425,988,1014]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" pagination="301 - 318" refId="ref79214" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Wei, M. - C. (2016) Leaf-rolling sawflies (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae, Pamphiliinae) of Tianmushan Mountains, Zhejiang Province, China. Zootaxa, 4072 (3), 301 - 318. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4072.3.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Shinohara &amp; Wei 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Molecular data are not available for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara &amp; Wei" authorityYear="2016" box="[558,639,1024,1050]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atra">
<emphasis box="[558,639,1024,1050]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. atra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but we have COI and NaK sequences for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Takeuchi" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[1117,1268,1024,1050]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minomalis">
<emphasis box="[1117,1268,1024,1050]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. minomalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1987" box="[1282,1389,1024,1050]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[1282,1389,1024,1050]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1987" box="[151,292,1060,1086]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yezoensis">
<emphasis box="[151,292,1060,1086]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. yezoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and they formed a clade with 100% UFBoot support in the COI and 99% UFBoot support in the NaK genes (
<figureCitation box="[232,335,1096,1122]" captionStart="FIGURE 139" captionStartId="228.[151,250,1667,1691]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,190,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-26@228.[151,1436,181,1643]" captionTargetPageId="228" captionText="FIGURE 139. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Onycholyda, part 2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876841/files/figure.png" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Figs 139</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[350,396,1096,1123]" captionStart="FIGURE 153" captionStartId="240.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[178,1407,186,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-26@240.[172,1415,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="240" captionText="FIGURE 153. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Onycholyda." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876872" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876872/files/figure.png" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">153</figureCitation>
). In the COI analysis, the two sequences of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1987" box="[909,1052,1096,1122]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yezoensis">
<emphasis box="[909,1052,1096,1122]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. yezoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differed by 0.1% and the nearest neighbour, diverging by a minimum of 2.3%, was 
<emphasis box="[726,842,1132,1158]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1987" box="[726,838,1132,1158]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">O. similis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
with which 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1987" box="[985,1127,1132,1158]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yezoensis">
<emphasis box="[985,1127,1132,1158]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. yezoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
formed a clade with 100% UFBoot support (
<figureCitation box="[346,444,1168,1194]" captionStart="FIGURE 139" captionStartId="228.[151,250,1667,1691]" captionTargetBox="[157,1426,190,1638]" captionTargetId="figure-26@228.[151,1436,181,1643]" captionTargetPageId="228" captionText="FIGURE 139. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Onycholyda, part 2." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876841" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876841/files/figure.png" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Fig. 139</figureCitation>
). In the NaK analysis, the two sequences of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1987" box="[932,1071,1168,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yezoensis">
<emphasis box="[932,1071,1168,1194]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. yezoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differed by 0.1% and the nearest neighbour, diverging by a minimum of 0%, was 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1987" box="[694,801,1204,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[694,801,1204,1230]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1437,808,1518]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<bibRefCitation author="Takeuchi, K." box="[199,397,1240,1266]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" pagination="53 - 108" refId="ref80403" refString="Takeuchi, K. (1936 a) Tenthredinoidea of Saghalien (Hymenoptera). Tenthredo, 1, 53 - 108." type="journal article" year="1936">Takeuchi (1936a)</bibRefCitation>
first recorded this species as “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Takeuchi" authorityYear="1936" box="[745,999,1240,1266]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Anoplolyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minomalis">
<emphasis box="[745,999,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Anoplolyda minomalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (= 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Takeuchi" authorityYear="1936" box="[1045,1197,1240,1266]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Anoplolyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minomalis">
<emphasis box="[1045,1197,1240,1266]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. minomalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) from 
<collectingRegion box="[1276,1378,1240,1266]" country="Russia" name="Sakhalin" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Sakhalin</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." pageId="66" pageNumber="67" pagination="346 - 359" refId="ref76075" refString="Shinohara, A. (1985 b) The sawfly genus Onycholyda (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) of Japan I. Kontyu, Tokyo, 53, 346 - 359." type="journal article" year="1985">Shinohara (1985b)</bibRefCitation>
, adopting a broader concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Takeuchi" authorityYear="1936" box="[674,825,1276,1302]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Anoplolyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minomalis">
<emphasis box="[674,825,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. minomalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, included 
<collectingRegion box="[941,1039,1276,1302]" country="Russia" name="Sakhalin" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Sakhalin</collectingRegion>
in the distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Takeuchi" authorityYear="1936" box="[1279,1430,1276,1302]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Anoplolyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minomalis">
<emphasis box="[1279,1430,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. minomalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[268,477,1312,1338]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" pagination="486 - 501" refId="ref76282" refString="Shinohara, A. (1987 a) The sawfly genus Onycholyda (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) of Japan V. Kontyu, Tokyo, 55, 486 - 501." type="journal article" year="1987">Shinohara (1987a)</bibRefCitation>
recognized three species in the previous concept of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Takeuchi" authorityYear="1936" box="[1076,1229,1312,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Anoplolyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minomalis">
<emphasis box="[1076,1229,1312,1338]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. minomalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and described the species occurring in 
<collectingRegion box="[387,497,1348,1374]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[556,654,1348,1374]" country="Russia" name="Sakhalin" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Sakhalin</collectingRegion>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1987" box="[694,836,1348,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yezoensis">
<emphasis box="[694,836,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. yezoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, thus excluding 
<collectingRegion box="[1026,1124,1348,1374]" country="Russia" name="Sakhalin" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Sakhalin</collectingRegion>
from the distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Takeuchi" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Anoplolyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minomalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. minomalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Zhelochovtsev, A. N. &amp; Zinovjev, A. G." box="[284,676,1384,1411]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" pagination="395 - 415" refId="ref81182" refString="Zhelochovtsev, A. N. &amp; Zinovjev, A. G. (1995) A list of the sawflies and horntails (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) of the fauna of Russia and adjacent territories. I. Entomologicheskoe Obozrenie, 74, 395 - 415. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1995">Zhelochovtsev &amp; Zinovjev (1995)</bibRefCitation>
correctly understood this history and noted “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara, 1987" authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1987" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yezoensis">
<emphasis box="[1200,1306,1385,1410]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">yezoensis</emphasis>
Shinohara, 1987
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Takeuchi" authorityYear="1936" box="[245,362,1420,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Anoplolyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minomalis">
<emphasis box="[245,362,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">minomalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auct., in part). — EFE”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundukov, Yu. N." box="[638,833,1420,1446]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" pagination="20 - 117" refId="ref79858" refString="Sundukov, Yu. N. (2017) Suborder Symphyta - Sawflies and wood wasps. In: Lelej, A. S., Proshchalykin, M. Yu. &amp; Loktionov, V. M. (Eds.), Annotated catalogue of the Hymenoptera of Russia. Vol. I. Symphyta and Apocrita: Aculeata. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the Russian Academy of Sciences, Supplement 6, pp. 20 - 117." type="journal article" year="2017">Sundukov (2017)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Takeuchi" authorityYear="1936" box="[942,1092,1420,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Anoplolyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minomalis">
<emphasis box="[942,1092,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. minomalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Russian fauna, probably according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[298,507,1456,1483]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" pagination="346 - 359" refId="ref76075" refString="Shinohara, A. (1985 b) The sawfly genus Onycholyda (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) of Japan I. Kontyu, Tokyo, 53, 346 - 359." type="journal article" year="1985">Shinohara (1985b)</bibRefCitation>
and neglecting 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[686,897,1456,1482]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" pagination="486 - 501" refId="ref76282" refString="Shinohara, A. (1987 a) The sawfly genus Onycholyda (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) of Japan V. Kontyu, Tokyo, 55, 486 - 501." type="journal article" year="1987">Shinohara (1987a)</bibRefCitation>
. Without further evidence, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Takeuchi" authorityYear="1936" box="[1203,1355,1456,1482]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Anoplolyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minomalis">
<emphasis box="[1203,1355,1456,1482]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">O. minomalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be excluded from the list of the Russian fauna.
</paragraph>
